Word at Tottenham's state-of-the-art Enfield training complex is that the club will make a concerted effort to sign Southampton striker Jay Rodriguez in January.

What's for sure is manager Mauricio Pochettino needs to inject some life into his misfiring forward line, sooner rather than later.

Wednesday night's Capital One Cup clash against Brighton merely underlined the White Hart Lane club's need for a shiny new striker once the transfer window re-opens.

