But with every passing 90 minutes, the Argentine knows he'll have to spend on a new striker in January.

His interest in Rodriguez, a player he worked with and helped nurture at St Mary's, is no secret.

There was a willingness, certainly from Pochettino, to strike a deal with the Saints for the England international in the summer.

The long-term knee injury Rodriguez sustained towards the end of last season was one of the crucial factors in Spurs decision not to show more commitment in their attempts to land the 25-year-old.

But Rodriguez is now approaching fitness; Pochettino knows it to, having been kept updated on his target's rehabilitation.

